title: Sidewall, 1870–90
provenance: From the "Upstairs East" room of West College, Williamstown, Massachusetts,built 1796.
creditline: Gift of Mrs. Henry N. Flynt
description: Aesthetic style. A symmetrical scrollwork and foliate figure which repeats very closely in drop-repeating relationship. Printed in cream and red on uncolored ground.

tombstone.epitaph:
Sidewall, 1870–90.
1870–90. Machine-printed. Gift of Mrs. Henry N. Flynt. 1955-41-2.
